  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_GeneralSectionTeachingTipContentTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Enable DeskBorder: turns edge switching, desktop creation, auto cleanup, and global hotkeys on or off together.
• Run at system startup: starts the app in the tray right after Windows sign-in.
• Check for Store updates: keeps update checks enabled for Store-distributed builds.
• Multi-display behavior: disables monitoring on multi-monitor setups, or limits it to the outermost display edges only.
• App language: pins the UI to a specific language or follows the system language.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_HotkeysSectionDescriptionTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Configure hotkeys that directly control DeskBorder, window movement, and Navigator.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_HotkeysSectionTitleTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Global hotkeys</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_HotkeysSectionTeachingTip.Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Global hotkey guide</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_HotkeysSectionTeachingTipContentTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Each global hotkey can be enabled or disabled independently.
• Combine a primary key with modifiers to configure the DeskBorder toggle, move focused window to previous desktop, move focused window to next desktop, and Navigator overlay toggle actions.
• The status indicator immediately shows whether the shortcut is valid, missing a key, duplicated, or failed to register.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_ImportExportSectionDescriptionTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
