  <data name="SettingsPage_NavigatorSectionTeachingTipContentTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Enable trigger area: when the pointer enters the configured screen region, the display-only Navigator mini map appears at the bottom of the monitor that currently contains the pointer.
• Select area: opens a selection overlay on the monitor that currently shows the settings window. The dragged rectangle is saved as-is, and the DeskBorder service pauses while you are selecting.
• If you also enable the Navigator mini map hotkey in the global hotkeys section, both the shortcut and mouse area triggers stay active together.</value>
  </data>
