  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_BlacklistSectionTeachingTipContentTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Add from running processes: lets you pick only currently running processes that are not already registered.
• Listed processes are excluded from edge switching, desktop creation, and auto deletion handling.
• Keep games or full-screen apps here when DeskBorder should not interfere with them.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_EdgeSectionTeachingTip.Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Edges and auto cleanup guide</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SettingsPage_EdgeSectionTeachingTipContentTextBlock.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Auto delete empty desktops: deletes an outer desktop when you move inward and it no longer has windows.
• Show deletion warning: when enabled, deletion waits briefly so you can undo it; when disabled, empty desktops are deleted immediately for continuous cleanup.
• Deletion warning timeout: adjusts how long the undo wait lasts while the deletion warning is shown.
• Empty desktop detection: a desktop counts as empty only when the wallpaper is actually visible. Minimized windows do not block auto deletion.
• Top and bottom ignore zones: adjusts, in percentages, how much of the upper and lower screen area should ignore edge switching and desktop creation.
• Enable desktop creation: turns the creation of a new desktop from the right edge of the last desktop on or off.
• Switch desktop modifiers: key combination that must be held before edge-based desktop switching triggers.
• Create desktop modifiers: key combination required to create a new desktop from the right edge of the last desktop.</value>
  </data>
